<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Support class for static dtor execution. For hosted (in-process) JITs</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><Highlight kind="comment">///        only!</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><Highlight kind="comment">///   If a &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit function isn&#39;t found C++ programs that use static</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><Highlight kind="comment">/// destructors will fail to link. However, we don&#39;t want to use the host</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><Highlight kind="comment">/// process&#39;s &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit, because it will schedule JIT&#39;d destructors to run</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><Highlight kind="comment">/// after the JIT has been torn down, which is no good. This class makes it easy</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to override &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit (and the related &#95;&#95;dso&#95;handle).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><Highlight kind="comment">///   To use, clients should manually call searchOverrides from their symbol</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment">/// resolver. This should generally be done after attempting symbol resolution</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment">/// inside the JIT, but before searching the host process&#39;s symbol table. When</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the client determines that destructors should be run (generally at JIT</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment">/// teardown or after a return from main), the runDestructors method should be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><Highlight kind="comment">/// called.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/localcxxruntimeoverridesbase"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/localcxxruntimeoverridesbase">LocalCXXRuntimeOverridesBase</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
